---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '@/components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="AEGIS — runtime safety for AI agents"
  description="Stop hallucinated tool calls before they hit production. Open-source agent firewall — zero code change, cryptographic audit, multi-tenant, SOC 2 framework. MIT licensed."
>
  <Header current="home" />

  <!-- ── HERO ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="eyebrow">Open-source · MIT licensed · v0.1.0</p>
        <h1>
          The runtime <em>safety layer</em><br/>
          for AI agents.
        </h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Every tool call your agent makes — classified, run through
          rules / ML / LLM-judge / DSL, and matched against per-tenant
          policy with fail-safe semantics. Before execution. Zero code
          change.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-cta">
          <a href="https://app.aegis.dev/signup" class="btn">Start free → app.aegis.dev</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/Justin0504/Aegis" class="btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View source</a>
        </div>
        <p class="hero-trust">
          Self-hosted via Docker · Hosted SaaS · Enterprise on-prem
          available · No credit card required for Free tier
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── ZERO CODE CHANGE ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="zero-code">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Zero code change · 5 minute integration</p>
        <h2>Two lines of env, no SDK rewrite.</h2>
        <p class="lede-2">
          AEGIS ships as an LLM egress proxy — point your existing
          OpenAI / Anthropic / Mistral / Gemini SDK at the gateway URL
          and every call flows through the detector chain, audit, and
          transparency log. Your code stays untouched.
        </p>
        <div class="snippet-grid">
          <div class="snippet">
            <div class="snippet-label">Before</div>
            <pre><code>import openai
client = openai.OpenAI(
    api_key="sk-xxxx"
)</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
          <div class="snippet">
            <div class="snippet-label">After (env only)</div>
            <pre><code><span class="hl">OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://gateway.aegis.dev/openai/v1
AEGIS_API_KEY=aeg_xxx</span>

# code unchanged</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="four-modes">
          Four integration modes: <strong>LLM egress proxy</strong> (zero
          code), <strong>SDK auto-instrument</strong> (1 line init),
          <strong>MCP proxy</strong> (one config field), or
          <strong>HTTP gateway</strong> (direct calls). Pick whichever
          matches your stack.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── PRODUCT HIGHLIGHTS ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="highlights">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Four things AEGIS does end-to-end</p>
        <h2>From repo scan to runtime block — one platform.</h2>
        <p class="lede-2">
          Most guardrail products start at the gateway. AEGIS starts at
          the moment you point it at your code: scan, generate policies,
          gate at deploy time, enforce at runtime, audit forever. Each
          step is its own product page; here's the 10-second tour.
        </p>

        <div class="hl-grid">
          <a class="hl" href="/features/scanner">
            <div class="hl-num">01</div>
            <h3>One-click workflow scanner</h3>
            <p>
              Point at any folder. Tree-sitter AST detection across
              Python / JS / TS / TSX. LangGraph / CrewAI / AutoGen /
              Mastra / Vercel-AI topology extraction. Tool inventory +
              entry-point ranking. No config, no annotation.
            </p>
            <span class="hl-cta">Read more →</span>
          </a>

          <a class="hl" href="/features/policy-generator">
            <div class="hl-num">02</div>
            <h3>Natural language → SOTA policy</h3>
            <p>
              One paragraph + the scanner's output in. A grammar-
              constrained policy bundle out, AJV-self-tested, repaired
              via PerFine if any test fails. Per-node policies keyed
              on real tool names — no inventing.
            </p>
            <span class="hl-cta">Read more →</span>
          </a>

          <a class="hl" href="/features/predeploy">
            <div class="hl-num">03</div>
            <h3>Pre-deployment scan + CI gate</h3>
            <p>
              GitHub Action emits SARIF. Build fails on secret leak,
              unsafe tool config, policy coverage gap, PI corpus
              regression, AAT-T* technique not covered. Catch it
              before it merges, not in production.
            </p>
            <span class="hl-cta">Read more →</span>
          </a>

          <a class="hl" href="/features/customize">
            <div class="hl-num">04</div>
            <h3>Customize every layer</h3>
            <p>
              YAML scan rules, TypeScript detector plugins, JSON
              policy DSL, tunable capability-risk weights, custom
              compliance bundles. Extend without forking — your
              customisations slot in alongside built-ins.
            </p>
            <span class="hl-cta">Read more →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── CAPABILITIES ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="caps">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">What AEGIS does that the rest doesn't</p>
        <h2>SOTA agent-security stack.</h2>

        <div class="cap-grid">
          <article class="cap">
            <h3>Cryptographic audit</h3>
            <p>RFC 6962 Merkle log + Sigstore-style witness cosignature.
              Customers verify any past event offline against a cached
              signed root — without trusting AEGIS infrastructure.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="cap">
            <h3>Sequence-aware anomaly</h3>
            <p>Per-agent n-gram language model over tool-call sequences
              (Witten-Bell smoothing). Catches the adversarial-shuffle
              attack class that independent-call scoring misses.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="cap">
            <h3>Multi-agent collusion</h3>
            <p>Cross-agent communication graph with handoff burst,
              sensitive relay, and cycle detection. Targets the SOTA
              failure mode named by Anthropic Agentic Misalignment 2025.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="cap">
            <h3>Workflow-aware policy gen</h3>
            <p>Scanner extracts LangGraph / CrewAI / AutoGen / Mastra /
              Vercel AI topology. AI generator writes per-node policies
              keyed on your real node ids — no inventing tool names.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="cap">
            <h3>NIST AI RMF risk scoring</h3>
            <p>Five-dimension capability scorer (action / egress /
              secrets / pii / scale). 0-100 composite with LOW / MEDIUM
              / HIGH / CRITICAL class and posture recommendations.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="cap">
            <h3>Built-in PI corpus</h3>
            <p>26 prompt-injection patterns × 6 categories from OWASP
              LLM Top 10, Promptfoo, Anthropic 2025, GandalfPro.
              Coverage report against your live policies.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="cap">
            <h3>Counterfactual explainer</h3>
            <p>When AEGIS blocks a call, it returns the minimum edit
              that WOULD have passed, verified by re-running the
              validator. NIST AI RMF + EU AI Act Art. 14 ready.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="cap">
            <h3>Policy effectiveness</h3>
            <p>Per-policy precision / recall / F1 over rolling window.
              Signal each policy HEALTHY / TIGHTEN / RETIRE / PROBE so
              operators retire noisy rules instead of acrobatic tuning.</p>
          </article>
        </div>

        <p class="caps-foot">
          See the <a href="https://github.com/Justin0504/Aegis/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md" rel="noopener">changelog</a>
          for the full set — 1,129 tests across 80+ suites, 25/25
          tables Postgres-ready, SCIM + SAML + OIDC for enterprise IdP.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── COMPARISON ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="vs">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">How AEGIS compares</p>
        <h2>Versus the AI-guardrail category.</h2>
        <p class="lede-2">
          The runtime safety layer for AI agents has converged on a
          handful of capabilities. Here is what AEGIS does versus
          Lakera Guard, Robust Intelligence (Cisco), Protect AI
          Guardian, and Calypso AI.
        </p>
        <div class="vs-scroll">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Capability</th><th>AEGIS</th><th>Others</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><th scope="row">Cryptographic audit (Merkle + witness)</th><td class="y">Built-in, RFC 6962</td><td class="n">none</td></tr>
              <tr><th scope="row">Sequence-aware anomaly</th><td class="y">n-gram LM, per-agent</td><td class="n">independent-call only</td></tr>
              <tr><th scope="row">Multi-agent collusion detection</th><td class="y">3 signals</td><td class="n">single-agent only</td></tr>
              <tr><th scope="row">Workflow-graph → per-node policy</th><td class="y">5 frameworks</td><td class="n">none</td></tr>
              <tr><th scope="row">Counterfactual explainer</th><td class="y">Verified by re-validation</td><td class="p">partial / log-only</td></tr>
              <tr><th scope="row">Custom AST scan rules</th><td class="y">Tree-sitter + YAML</td><td class="p">regex only</td></tr>
              <tr><th scope="row">GenAI OpenTelemetry semconv</th><td class="y">Full + guardrail ext</td><td class="p">proprietary</td></tr>
              <tr><th scope="row">SCIM 2.0 + SAML + OIDC</th><td class="y">All three</td><td class="p">one or the other</td></tr>
              <tr><th scope="row">Policy effectiveness scoring</th><td class="y">P/R/F1 + retire signal</td><td class="n">none</td></tr>
              <tr><th scope="row">License</th><td class="y">MIT</td><td class="n">closed source</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="vs-foot">
          "Others" reflects the largest public documentation across
          Lakera Guard, Robust Intelligence AI Firewall, Protect AI
          Guardian, Calypso AI Moderator circa June 2026. Send
          corrections to
          <a href="mailto:security@aegis.dev">security@aegis.dev</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── CTA STRIP ─────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="cta-strip">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Ship one env var. Block your first hallucinated tool call this afternoon.</h2>
        <div class="cta-buttons">
          <a href="https://app.aegis.dev/signup" class="btn">Start free</a>
          <a href="/pricing" class="btn-secondary">See pricing</a>
        </div>
        <p class="muted small">
          1,000 requests/month + 7-day audit retention on the Free
          tier. No credit card. Self-host the same gateway via
          <code>docker compose up</code> if you'd rather run it locally.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />

  <style>
    main { padding: 0; }
    .hero { padding: 6rem 0 4rem; }
    .eyebrow {
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      font-weight: 500;
    }
    .hero h1 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); }
    .lede {
      max-width: 56ch;
      font-size: 1.18rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 1.2rem 0 2rem;
    }
    .hero-cta {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.8rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .hero-trust {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.86rem;
      margin: 0.8rem 0 0;
    }

    /* Zero code change */
    .zero-code { padding: 4rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline); }
    .section-eyebrow {
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      font-weight: 500;
    }
    .lede-2 {
      max-width: 60ch;
      font-size: 1.04rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 0 0 2rem;
    }
    .snippet-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
      align-items: stretch;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
    }
    .snippet {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    }
    .snippet pre {
      background: transparent;
      border: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0;
    }
    .snippet-label {
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    }
    .hl { background: var(--accent); color: var(--bg); padding: 0 2px; }
    .arrow {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-size: 1.6rem;
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .four-modes {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      max-width: 70ch;
    }
    .four-modes strong { color: var(--text); }
    @media (max-width: 760px) {
      .snippet-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .arrow { transform: rotate(90deg); }
    }

    /* Capability grid */
    /* Product highlights — 4-card spotlight after zero-code, before vs-table */
    .highlights {
      padding: 4rem 0;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
      background: var(--surface);
    }
    .highlights h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); margin: 0.3rem 0 0.8rem; }
    .hl-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
      gap: 1.2rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }
    .hl {
      display: block;
      background: var(--bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1.6rem 1.4rem 1.3rem;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: var(--text);
      transition: border-color 0.15s, transform 0.05s;
      position: relative;
    }
    .hl:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }
    .hl:active { transform: translateY(1px); }
    .hl-num {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 0.86rem;
      color: var(--accent-warn);
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    }
    .hl h3 {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    }
    .hl p {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.94rem;
      margin: 0 0 0.9rem;
    }
    .hl-cta {
      font-weight: 500;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    .caps { padding: 4rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline); }
    .cap-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
      gap: 1.4rem;
      margin: 2rem 0 1.5rem;
    }
    .cap {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 1.2rem 1.2rem;
    }
    .cap h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
    .cap p { margin: 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.93rem; line-height: 1.55; }
    .caps-foot { color: var(--muted); margin-top: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.92rem; }

    /* Comparison */
    .vs { padding: 4rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline); }
    .vs-scroll { overflow-x: auto; }
    .vs table {
      width: 100%;
      min-width: 620px;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }
    .vs thead th {
      text-align: left;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--muted);
      padding: 0.6rem 0.9rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    }
    .vs tbody th[scope="row"] {
      text-align: left;
      font-weight: 500;
      padding: 0.72rem 0.9rem;
      color: var(--text);
      width: 48%;
    }
    .vs tbody td { padding: 0.72rem 0.9rem; width: 26%; vertical-align: top; }
    .vs tbody tr + tr { border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline); }
    .vs tbody td.y { color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }
    .vs tbody td.y::before { content: "✓ "; color: var(--accent-positive); font-weight: 700; }
    .vs tbody td.p { color: var(--muted); }
    .vs tbody td.p::before { content: "◐ "; color: var(--accent-warn); font-weight: 700; }
    .vs tbody td.n { color: var(--muted); }
    .vs tbody td.n::before { content: "✗ "; color: var(--accent-error); font-weight: 700; }
    .vs-foot { color: var(--muted); margin-top: 1.2rem; font-size: 0.82rem; max-width: 62ch; }

    /* CTA strip */
    .cta-strip {
      padding: 4rem 0;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
      background: var(--surface);
    }
    .cta-strip h2 { max-width: 22ch; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 0.8rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
    .muted { color: var(--muted); }
    .small { font-size: 0.86rem; max-width: 60ch; }
  </style>
</Layout>
